The name (
cingulatus
) refers to the conspicuous dark brown transversal patch on the first gastral tergite of workers of this species.

caption.paragraph:
Figures 18-20.

Nesomyrmex cingulatus

sp. n. holotype worker (CASENT0919845). Head in full-face view (
18
), dorsal view of the body (
19
), lateral view of the body (
20
).

subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is known to occur in the spiny forests of the southern part of Madagascar from 40-400 m (
Fig. 21
). The known samples are collected from live stems.
